The `&lt;2&gt;` is not in line, because you didn&#39;t provide _well-formed_ XML code. To make your &quot;XML&quot; code _well-formed_, you should transform it to something like this:

    &lt;Numbers&gt;
      &lt;1 /&gt;
      &lt;2 /&gt;
      &lt;3 /&gt;
    &lt;/Numbers&gt;

or

    &lt;Numbers&gt;
      &lt;1&gt;
         &lt;2 /&gt;
      &lt;/1&gt;
      &lt;3 /&gt;
    &lt;/Numbers&gt;

**Finally:**  
According to the [XML specification v1.1](https://www.w3.org/TR/xml-c14n/) an [NTName](https://www.w3.org/TR/REC-xml/#NT-Name) cannot start with a number. It must start with a [NameStartChar](https://www.w3.org/TR/REC-xml/#NT-NameStartChar) (But I guess that your naming scheme was only for illustrative purposes).

Taking all of this into account, the result should be as expected.

